d). Since she loaded on Christmas we see a bit higher overtime costs from tugs, lines, etc. but port costs in Houston remain about $13k less than predicted. With additional waiting time we still managed to save on bunkers with vessel underconsuming and MGO $22/mt less than expected."},{"modifiedDate":"2020-12-17T15:19:10.23","modifiedByFull":"Bradbury, Mike","remark":"B. LAYCAN      : 23 - 25 DECEMBER (0001-1600) 2020\nTO BE NARROWED TO ONE DAY IN CHARTERER\u0027S OPTION"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}